Package: reach.io
Title: Data IO for the flode environment
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Jonathan", "Payne", , "jon.payne@environment-agency.gov.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2551-5353"))
Description: A hydrometric data pipeline toolkit for the Environment Agency
    Hydrology API <https://environment.data.gov.uk/hydrology/doc/reference>.
    Provides tools to query and download rainfall, flow, and water level data
    via synchronous and batch methods; build and maintain a master gauge
    registry; route gauge fetches to the correct source system (HDE, WISKI,
    or bulk file); ingest historical bulk files into partitioned Parquet
    (Bronze tier); and orchestrate parallelised backfills across thousands
    of gauges with per-gauge logging and failure recovery.
